  "title": "Warehouse Assistant",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Perform logistics duties including receiving, put-away, checking, retrieving, loading and unloading, repacking, and palletizing of import and export cargo, in accordance with Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs).</li>\n  <li>Handle all goods with care to prevent damage or loss.</li>\n  <li>Assist in conducting physical inventory counts to ensure stock accuracy.</li>\n  <li>Maintain proper usage and upkeep of material handling equipment.</li>\n  <li>Carry out general housekeeping tasks and contribute to a clean and safe work environment.</li>\n  <li>Operate forklifts and reach trucks, if appropriately licensed and trained.</li>\n  <li>Comply with all company policies and procedures related to quality control, safety, and security.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Possess Secondary school education, NITEC, or equivalent in Logistics or related field</li>\n  <li>1–3 years of experience in warehouse/logistics operations will be added advantages</li>\n  <li>Valid forklift license.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R22110981</p>\n<p>EA Personnel Name: Law Mei Fong</p>\n<p><br></p>",
